Argentina IT is an international platform designed to facilitate insertion and consolidation of Argentine software and IT services into attractive world markets.In April 2013, the signing of the Founding Regulation by the first 34 member companies took place, opening offices in five countries: Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Mexico, and the U.S.Javier's key responsibilities include developing overseas business, strengthening the relationship between client companies, promoting partnerships and joint developments, innovation and cooperation.

FTG LLC is a family owned Real Estate company, dedicated to investing and building family and commercial buildings, with presence in France, US, and Argentina. Javier was responsible for setting up the operations in Argentina, involved in the different activities.Javier participated in two main Land Trust Projects: Solares l & ll (US$ 1.7 M.), based in Córdoba, building up to 50 family apartments. The main tasks included managing investor relationships, budget presentation, strategic and business planning.Javier also conducted market research, participated in pre-sales and sales, contract negotiation and generated potential customers and investors databases.  Currently, FTG LLC manages different rentals and is investing in Soybean fields and grape vineyards in Córdoba and Mendoza.

Club TQ is the largest Amateur Soccer Tournament Organization in the interior of Argentina, producing sport events and marketing campaigns for individuals and companies, both in the online and offline world.With over 7 years of experience, it has the largest number of teams registered in Mendoza and Córdoba. Chosen by young people between 18 and 35 years, the Tournaments guarantee entertainment and outdoor physical activity ensuring a fun and social gathering.Some of the featured clients and sponsors are: Quilmes, Gatorade, Subway and Fiat. Club TQ got 60% of market share, with more than 1500 players in it's first three years.

summary: IT Entrepreneur, with experience in different successful start-ups in different industries.Javier was born and raised in "The Land of Sun and Good Wine". His curiosity led him to start travelling extensively at very young age, throughout Europe, America and Asia.While studying at College he co-founded Club TQ, the largest amateur Soccer Tournament in the interior of Argentina based on a sophisticated website to track every player and team data.Javier also participated in the start up of FTG LLC operations in Argentina; a family Real Estate company with presence in Europe and United States. He was involved in developing Land Trusts for Familiy Buildings. This opportunity enabled Javier to gain experience in managing large scale complex Projects successfully.After graduation, Javier went to the "Big City" to pursue an MBA at IAE Business School, where he started incubating his next venture and co-founded WillDom, a top notch IT Business Ecosystem, where each member contributes to creating world class value.Presently, Javier co-leads WillDom, specializing in Offshore Outsourcing Services from Latin America including:- Software/Application/ Product engineering services- Web application Development Services- Games Dynamics - Mobile Platforms- Quality Assurance ServicesIn his time off, Javier enjoys Life, reading, sipping a great Malbec, playing Capoeira, skiing in Colorado, scuba diving in the Andaman Sea and having an "asado" among friends.
